Big Data Roadmap (Zero to Hero)
│
├── 1. Basics of Programming and Databases
│   ├── Programming Languages
│   │   ├── Python (Data Analysis Libraries: Pandas, NumPy)
│   │   ├── Java (For Hadoop, Spark)
│   │   └── Scala (For Apache Spark)
│   ├── SQL Basics
│   │   ├── SQL Queries (SELECT, JOIN, GROUP BY)
│   │   ├── Database Concepts (ACID, Normalization)
│   │   └── Indexing, Views, Stored Procedures
│   └── NoSQL Basics
│       ├── Document Stores (MongoDB)
│       ├── Key-Value Stores (Redis)
│       └── Columnar Databases (Cassandra, HBase)
│
├── 2. Linux and Shell Scripting
│   ├── Basic Shell Commands
│   ├── File Systems (Linux-based clusters)
│   ├── Process Management
│   ├── Scheduling Scripts (Cron Jobs)
│   └── Automating Tasks with Shell Scripting
│
├── 3. Data Structures and Algorithms
│   ├── Basics of Data Structures
│   │   ├── Arrays, Lists, Hashmaps
│   │   ├── Trees and Graphs
│   │   └── Queues and Stacks
│   └── Algorithms for Big Data
│       ├── Sorting, Searching
│       ├── MapReduce Algorithms
│       └── Distributed Data Processing
│
├── 4. Distributed Systems and Big Data Ecosystem
│   ├── Distributed Systems Concepts
│   │   ├── CAP Theorem
│   │   ├── Consistency, Availability, Partition Tolerance
│   │   └── Data Replication and Sharding
│   ├── Big Data Ecosystem Overview
│   │   ├── Hadoop Ecosystem (HDFS, YARN, MapReduce)
│   │   └── Apache Spark Ecosystem (RDDs, DataFrames, Datasets)
│
├── 5. Hadoop Ecosystem
│   ├── Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS)
│   │   ├── Data Replication and Storage
│   │   └── Writing and Reading Files from HDFS
│   ├── MapReduce Programming
│   │   ├── Map, Shuffle, Reduce Phases
│   │   └── Writing MapReduce Jobs in Java/Python
│   ├── YARN (Yet Another Resource Negotiator)
│   │   ├── Resource Allocation in Hadoop
│   │   └── Running Applications on Hadoop Cluster
│   └── Hive and Pig
│       ├── HiveQL (SQL on Hadoop)
│       └── Dataflow Programming with Pig
│
├── 6. Apache Spark Ecosystem
│   ├── Spark Core
│   │   ├── Resilient Distributed Datasets (RDD)
│   │   ├── Spark Transformations and Actions
│   │   └── Lazy Evaluation in Spark
│   ├── Spark SQL
│   │   ├── DataFrames and Datasets
│   │   └── Query Optimization (Catalyst Optimizer)
│   ├── Spark Streaming
│   │   ├── Micro-batch Processing
│   │   ├── Structured Streaming
│   └── Spark MLlib
│       ├── Machine Learning Pipelines in Spark
│       └── Common ML Algorithms (Clustering, Regression)
│
├── 7. NoSQL Databases and Storage Systems
│   ├── HBase
│   │   ├── Column-Oriented Storage
│   │   ├── Reading and Writing to HBase Tables
│   └── Cassandra
│       ├── Key Concepts (Partitioning, Replication)
│       └── CQL (Cassandra Query Language)
│
├── 8. Data Ingestion and ETL Pipelines
│   ├── ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) Basics
│   │   └── Batch and Real-time Data Processing
│   ├── Apache Kafka
│   │   ├── Kafka Producers and Consumers
│   │   ├── Kafka Topics and Partitions
│   │   └── Kafka Streams for Real-time Processing
│   └── Apache NiFi
│       ├── Data Ingestion with NiFi
│       └── Building Data Flows for ETL
│
├── 9. Data Warehousing and Data Lakes
│   ├── Data Lakes
│   │   └── Storing Unstructured and Structured Data
│   ├── Apache Hive
│   │   ├── SQL Queries on HDFS
│   │   └── Partitioning and Bucketing Data
│   ├── Amazon Redshift (Cloud Data Warehouse)
│   ├── Google BigQuery
│   └── Snowflake
│
├── 10. Cloud and Big Data as a Service (BDaaS)
│   ├── AWS Big Data Services
│   │   ├── Amazon EMR (Elastic MapReduce)
│   │   ├── S3 (Storage)
│   │   ├── Athena (Querying S3)
│   │   └── AWS Glue (ETL)
│   ├── Google Cloud Big Data
│   │   ├── Google BigQuery
│   │   ├── Google Cloud Dataproc (Hadoop and Spark)
│   └── Microsoft Azure
│       ├── Azure Data Lake Storage
│       └── HDInsight (Hadoop, Spark)
│
├── 11. Data Visualization and Analytics
│   ├── Visualization Tools
│   │   ├── Tableau
│   │   ├── Power BI
│   │   └── Google Data Studio
│   ├── Apache Superset (Open-source BI Tool)
│   └── Data Analytics Platforms
│       └── Druid, Presto
│
├── 12. Machine Learning and Big Data
│   ├── Machine Learning Concepts
│   │   ├── Supervised and Unsupervised Learning
│   │   └── Common Algorithms (Linear Regression, Clustering)
│   ├── Spark MLlib
│   │   └── Building ML Pipelines in Spark
│   ├── TensorFlow with Big Data
│   ├── H2O.ai (Scalable ML)
│   └── DataRobot
│
├── 13. Data Governance and Security
│   ├── Data Privacy and Compliance (GDPR, HIPAA)
│   ├── Data Encryption and Secure Storage
│   ├── Kerberos Authentication in Hadoop
│   ├── Ranger and Sentry (Hadoop Security Tools)
│   └── Data Auditing and Monitoring Tools
│
├── 14. Monitoring and Debugging Big Data Pipelines
│   ├── Monitoring Tools
│   │   ├── Prometheus + Grafana
│   │   ├── Elasticsearch for Logs
│   └── Debugging Techniques
│       └── Spark UI, Hadoop YARN UI for Job Debugging
│
└── 15. Soft Skills and Communication
    ├── Collaboration with Data Scientists and Engineers
    ├── Documentation (ETL Pipelines, Data Governance Policies)
    ├── Communicating Insights from Big Data Analytics
    └── Project Management in Big Data Environments
